# Global CSS (`src/index.css`)

## Role

- Single entry for **`@import "tailwindcss"`**, **`@custom-variant dark`** (class-based, targeting `.dark` on root), and **`@theme`** semantic color mappings.
- **`:root` / `.dark`** hold CSS variables consumed by `@theme` (e.g. `--app-bg`, `--app-accent`).

## Rules

- Do not add page-specific layout rules here — use Tailwind in components.
- New brand or status colors: add a **CSS variable** in `:root` and `.dark`, then wire **`@theme --color-*`** so utilities like `bg-background` stay available.
- Keep **typography defaults** minimal (`html`, `body`, `#root`); prefer component utilities for one-off sizes.
